            <p class="faq-a">A stock split divides a company's existing shares into multiple new shares to boost liquidity. The total dollar value of the shares remains the same, as the share price drops proportionately. For example, in a 2-for-1 split, you get twice as many shares, but each share is worth half as much.</p>
